  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA33-kiḷavi">itu pirivuṇarttappaṭṭa talaimakaḷatu kuṟippaṟinta tōḻi talaimakaṟkuc colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what was said to HIM by the confidante who had understood the intention of HER who had been informed of the separation.</p>
      </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA33">
<l>            paṭucuṭa raṭainta paḵvāy neṭuvarai</l>
<l>            murampucēr ciṟukuṭip paranta mālaip</l>
<l>            pulampukūṭ ṭuṇṇum pulleṉ maṉṟattuk</l>
<l>            kalluṭaip paṭuviṟ kaluḻi tantu</l>
<l>            niṟaipeya laṟiyāk kuṟaikkū ṇalliṟ </l>
<l>            ṟuvarcey yāṭaic centoṭai maṟava</l>
<l>            ratarpārt talku mañcuvaru neṟiyiṭai</l>
<l>            yiṟappa veṇṇuva ravareṉiṉ maṟuttal</l>
<l>            valluvaṅ kollō melliya ṉāmeṉa</l>
<l>            vimmuṟu kiḷaviya ḷeṉmuka nōkki </l>
<l>            nallaka vaṉamulaik karaicērpu</l>
<l>            malkupuṉal paranta malarēr kaṇṇē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>[Her] blossom-like eyes spread<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">paranta</term> presumably has to be read as a finite verb n.pl. (cf. NA 5 <term xml:lang="ta">payanta</term>).</note> an increasing flood,</l>
<l rend="indent">joining the shore of the beautiful breasts in [her] good bosom,</l>
<l rend="indent2">as [she] looked into my face, she of heavy words:</l>
<l>“if he says he considers to traverse in between the fearsome paths<note place="foot">Here it is also possible to take <term xml:lang="ta">neṟi-y-iṭai</term> as a kind of intensifying synonym compound: "paths [and] ways".</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent">where the bold ones with straight arrows, dresses made with coral, </l>
<l rend="indent4">stay peering out at the way,</l>
<l rend="indent">[their] good houses crowded by wants that do not know of full rain, </l>
<l rend="indent">muddy water being brought<note place="foot">The <term xml:lang="ta">tantu</term> clause has no strict relation to the rest ‒-whether this is to be called an anacoluthic construction is a matter open to discussion.</note> from the stony well </l>
<l rend="indent">on the village common, empty, where they eat together in loneliness,</l>
<l rend="indent2">in evenings that spread over little homes joining the mounts of gravel </l>
<l rend="indent2">on the long mountain with many openings reached by the glow of the setting [sun],</l>
<l>will we be able to refuse, we who are of soft nature?”<note place="foot">Or, with the mss., another main question: "will we be able slowly to forget?"</note></l>
        </lg>
         </div>
          </body>
            </text>
